08/05/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Interior Minister Hari Kostov marked Police Day on Wednesday (7 May) by assuring the public that the security situation in Macedonia has improved.
He reiterated that the government would react to any destabilisation attempt, and is working with Albania to thwart any cross-border criminal activity.
In other news, a unit of the Macedonian Army is participating in an international military exercise that began Thursday in Germany.
It is part of NATO's Partnership for Peace programme.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 08/05/03;
A1 TV, MIA - 07/05/03)
